<div class="bolt-instructions">
  <h2>How to Take the BOLT Test</h2>
  
  <div class="instruction-steps">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">1</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Sit comfortably and relax</h3>
        <p>Find a quiet place where you can sit upright and be comfortable without distractions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">2</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Normal breathing</h3>
        <p>Breathe normally through your nose for about 30 seconds.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">3</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Hold your breath</h3>
        <p>Take a normal breath in and out through your nose. Pinch your nose and start the timer.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">4</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Stop the test</h3>
        <p>Hold until you feel the <strong>first</strong> urge to breathe. Stop the timer immediately.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">5</div>
      <div class="step-content">
        <h3>Record your score</h3>
        <p>Your BOLT score is the number of seconds you were able to hold your breath comfortably.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="important-note">
    <h3>Important:</h3>
    <p>The BOLT test is a comfortable breath hold. Stop at the first signs of discomfort, not at your maximum breath hold time.</p>
  </div>
</div>

